e in these two contrasting territories are participating in peace, the authors explore different forms of local agency, the progress they have, or have not, made, and the lessons that these local experiences might offer for peacebuilding elsewhere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPeace-buildingzColombia. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh1 aLombard, Melanie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLouise Turton, Helen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLópez-Lizarazo, Luz Mery, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMario Díaz-Arévalo, Juan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMiguel Kanai, Juan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRuiz-Galvan, Adriel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRushton, Simon, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aShesterinina, Anastasia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStaples, Henry, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978152922998140uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529230000?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529230000423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529230000/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles